{
  "texts": [
    "Following alignment, four ROIs were selected based on the H&E image from the Visium dataset using the napari-spatial data plugin, and these ROIs were then added to the aligned Xenium replicates.",
    "Each ROI was selected based on its distinct microanatomical characteristics and then labeled manually based on the underlying cell-type composition from the Xenium replicates.",
    "We used CopyKat (v.1.1.0) 18 with default parameters to estimate copy number states from the Visium count matrix followed by hierarchical clustering, which identified three major clusters on the locations labeled as ʻaneuploidʼ; these three clusters were used as genetic subclones.",
    "We also transferred clone labels to overlapping cells from Xenium replicates; these labels were stored as a SpatialData table element.",
    "This analysis was conducted in R separately (the notebooks repository: https://github.com/scverse/spatialdata-notebooks/tree/ main/notebooks/paper_reproducibility)."
  ]
}